---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
	title="ThingsBoard License Portal Privacy Policy"
	description="ThingsBoard License Portal (web-portal)"
>
	<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p class="date">Last Updated: January 16, 2026</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>1. Introduction</b></p>
	<p>
		This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the
		ThingsBoard Licensing Portal (the "Portal"). By using the Portal, you agree to the collection
		and use of information in accordance with this policy.
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>2. Information We Collect</b></p>
	<p>To provide our licensing services, we collect the following types of data:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Account Information:</b> Your name, email address, and login credentials created during
			sign-up.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Billing Information:</b> We do not collect or store your financial payment data. All
			billing-related data (including credit card details, billing addresses, and Tax IDs) is
			collected, processed, and stored directly by our third-party payment processor, Stripe.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>License & Usage Data:</b> We collect information regarding the license keys you generate,
			unbundle, or delete. Additionally, via our automated license check mechanism, we collect
			technical data regarding your hosting environment and the specific version of the licensed
			product you are currently running.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p><b>3. How We Use Your Information</b></p>
	<p>We use your data for the following purposes:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><b>Service Provision:</b> To create your account and verify your identity.</li>
		<li>
			<b>License Verification:</b> To validate the status of your software licenses, ensure
			compliance with usage terms, and identify product versions for support or compatibility
			purposes.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Transaction Processing:</b> To facilitate the secure processing of payments through Stripe.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Communication:</b> To send you transaction confirmations, technical notices, and use for
			providing support.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>4. Data Sharing</b></p>
	<p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Payment Processors (Stripe):</b> We integrate with Stripe to handle all billing and
			payment functions. Their use of your personal information is governed by their own Privacy
			Policy.
		</li>
		<li><b>Legal Compliance:</b> If required by law, regulation, or legal process.</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>5. Data Retention & Deletion</b></p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Retention:</b> We retain your account and license history for as long as your account is
			active or as needed to comply with our legal obligations.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Account Deletion:</b> You may delete your user or company account at any time through the
			Portal settings. Upon deletion, your access to the Portal is removed.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<br />

	<p><b>6. Security</b></p>
	<p>
		We implement reasonable security measures to protect your account information. As noted,
		sensitive billing data is secured and managed exclusively by Stripe in accordance with industry
		standards (PCI-DSS).
	</p>

	<br />

	<p><b>7. Contact Us</b></p>
	<p>
		If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at <a
			href="mailto:sales@thingsboard.io">sales@thingsboard.io</a
		>.
	</p>
</LegalLayout>